main event: Two circular unidentified flying objects were observed near Cape Canaveral, Florida on November 4, 1961.
interesting points: The observation lasted for about 5 minutes with the objects viewed separately 5 minutes apart., The objects were described as having a circular shape and the size of basketballs., The objects were reported to be very bright green in color., No sound was heard during the sighting., The sighting conditions were excellent with no optical aids used.
witness description: machine shop operator for Pan American Airways, 24 years of age
